{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "First, as a visual object, a network can be transparently presented to a stakeholder to summarize key elements of an interview, such as the list of factors deemed relevant by the stakeholder and their relationships.",
    "For example, a visual depiction of a system can help participants engage with data and discuss its implications (Conte and Davidson, 2020; Giabbanelli and Vesuvala, 2023), while pedagogical initiatives that emphasize systems thinking have often asked learners to create maps as a means to organize concepts regarding a problem domain (Schultz et al., 2022).",
    "Second, as a mathematical construct, a network can be analyzed to reveal important information about a person's mental model of a system (Blacketer et al., 2021), compare the views of individual stakeholders or groups (Aminpour et al., 2021), identify structural barriers or unintended consequences of interventions (Giabbanelli, Rice, et al., 2022), or reduce the complexity of a large map to its core themes (Hayward et al., 2020).",
    "The aforementioned benefits can only be unlocked once a network representation has been obtained.",
    "There has thus been considerable interest in automatically deriving networks from data."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, a visual depiction of a system can help participants engage with data and discuss its implications (Conte and Davidson, 2020; Giabbanelli and Vesuvala, 2023), while pedagogical initiatives that emphasize systems thinking have often asked learners to create maps as a means to organize concepts regarding a problem domain (Schultz et al., 2022).",
    "Second, as a mathematical construct, a network can be analyzed to reveal important information about a person's mental model of a system (Blacketer et al., 2021), compare the views of individual stakeholders or groups (Aminpour et al., 2021), identify structural barriers or unintended consequences of interventions (Giabbanelli, Rice, et al., 2022), or reduce the complexity of a large map to its core themes (Hayward et al., 2020)."
